title: Odessa Fire Rescue respond to structure, grass fire
content: Odessa Fire Rescue responded to a structure fire around 3 p.m. on June 2.  The fire started in the 2200 block of W. 2nd Street in Odessa.  It reportedly started on the train tracks before turning into a grass fire. This in turn ignited the building.  The fire took about an hour to put out. No injuries have been reported but the building is a total loss.  Download the free news app today  Click here to download for iPhone Click here to download for Android
